                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 24595/5.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Chargé <persName type="to">Monroe</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Wilson informs the legation that the Red Cross proposes a further expenditure
                    of $2,500 for material for building shelters, to be shipped on May 24 from New
                    Orleans. Instructs legation to telegraph suggestions as to material, quality,
                    general dimensions, etc.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
